Market Dynamics
The breakfast cereal market is influenced by several key dynamics:
•	Changing Consumer Preferences: Consumers are increasingly seeking healthier options, leading to a rise in demand for whole grain, gluten-free, and organic cereals.
•	Technological Advancements: Advances in food processing technology have enabled the creation of novel textures, flavors, and shapes, expanding consumer options.
•	Convenience and Nutrition: The convenience of breakfast cereals, combined with their nutritional benefits, makes them an attractive choice for busy individuals and families.
Market Size and Growth
As per Intent Market Research, the Breakfast Cereal Market was valued at USD 53.8 billion in 2023 and will surpass USD 87.4 billion by 2030; growing at a CAGR of 7.2% during 2024 - 2030.
